{
  "name": "Fudgy + Chewy Protein Brownies",
  "description": "The balanced one — derived from the Fudgy base, keeping real fudge from butter + baking chocolate but adding chew: the whole egg + an extra egg white are beaten with brown sugar until glossy (dissolved, never whipped to a ribbon), the cornstarch is dropped, and protein is doubled. 1/4 cup granulated Splenda, no added milk, baked at 325F for ~17-18 min and pulled at a slight (fudgy-leaning) jiggle. Doubling protein at flat calories pulls the ratio from the base's 16.6 down to 12.5 cal per g protein. Computed ~614 cal / 49 g protein per batch of 9; ~68 cal, 5.5P, 6.7C, 2.7F per square. Medium eggs (44 g whole, 30 g white). Source: user.",
  "tags": [
    "brownie",
    "protein",
    "fudgy",
    "chewy"
  ],
  "yield": {
    "amount": 9,
    "unit": "squares"
  },
